They lean toward familiar routines and carefully researched choices rather than adventurous experiments, and they often delay firm plans until closer to the moment, which lets them stay flexible but sometimes creates last-minute pressure. Socially reserved, they favor one-on-one or small-group interactions and are more comfortable listening than leading. They are strongly motivated by concern for others—frequently offering help, smoothing conflicts, and prioritizing inclusive, gentle solutions. At the same time they experience worry and sensitivity: uncertainty can produce tangible anxiety, so they prepare backup plans and rely on trusted companions for reassurance when situations feel unpredictable.

Socially reserved, they favor one-on-one or small-group interactions and are more comfortable listening than leading. They are strongly motivated by concern for others—frequently offering help, smoothing conflicts, and prioritizing inclusive, gentle solutions. At the same time they experience worry and sensitivity: uncertainty can produce tangible anxiety, so they prepare backup plans and rely on trusted companions for reassurance when situations feel unpredictable.
